description: This Jet Ski has a blown engine.  The Front Piston had a broken ring.. In my opinion its possible to rebuild the top end only and have a functional Jet ski. I have the title for the machine. Prior to the engine failure.. The Jet pump was rebuilt and re sleeved. The Impeller was rebuilt as well.  The seal where the drive shaft meets the hull/water was also replaced recently I had spent $1500 on a SBT engine .. 2 years later the engine failed again. This machine has been sitting in my garage for the past 3 years. I simply do not have any time for it anymore and I don't want to invest anymore money into it. The condition of the machine is " good"  IT looks great from the top and cleans up really well.  The hull has had a few repairs.. This machine used to be run in the Delaware river so its seen its fair share of rock damage.   There however are no leaks on the machine and the hull is in good working order.
